  "description": "This dataset comprises magnetoencephalography (MEG) recordings from human subjects performing a sequential conflict task. The study investigates the neural mechanisms of conflict detection, with particular focus on cortico-subthalamic interactions and beta-band oscillatory dynamics. Recordings include both healthy controls and Parkinson's disease patients, enabling examination of how conflict processing is modulated across different neurological conditions. This dataset is mirrored on NEMAR from the OpenNeuro repository (ds002908).",
